5:
Still sleeping, Alice? You're going to 
miss breakfast, you know.
26:
L-LIGHT?!
Who gave you permission to come 
into my room?!
29:
My apologies. You didn't come to 
breakfast, so I... More importantly, 
are you okay?
36:
You were having a bad dream. But it 
looks like you're fine now.
39:
Oh, geez... I didn't say anything weird, 
did I?
41:
Not particularly. Although you did call 
me "mama".
49:
No need to be embarrassed. It's 
perfectly normal to long for one's 
mother.
54:
I don't wanna hear that from you, 
you dumb furball!
64:
Oof... I'm guessing something 
happened to Alice. How did she even 
get up there, anyway?
68:
She floated onto the roof using her 
parasol.
76:
I'm sorry if I said anything to offend 
you, Alice. Won't you come back 
down?
79:
Hmph! I'll bet you don't even know 
WHY I'm mad at you!
87:
Well? Let's hear what you think this is 
all about then!
90:
Er... Was it because I berated you for 
sleeping in?
92:
I'm sorry. You're still a growing child, 
so you need your rest.
97:
Seriously?!
You REALLY don't have any idea, do 
you? I'm not coming down until I get 
a proper apology!
102:
Aliiice... we have paaancaaakes. 
They're niiice and fluuuffyyy.
106:
F-fluffy pancakes... I mean, hmph!
You really think I'm that simple?
107:
I've made it this far on my own! In 
some places, they call me the Marine 
Nightmare! I'm NOT a child, I'll have 
you know!
111:
But you still are a child. There's no way
you've—
115:
...!
That's where you're wrong. These 
aren't any ordinary pancakes, Alice!
119: What do you mean? They're ju—
127:
We've prepared a special set of 
pancakes for refined ladies such as 
yourself, Alice.
131:
Th-that's right. Made especially for 
you. A flavor only true ladies can 
appreciate—gourmet buttermilk and 
pancakes... with chocolate.
139:
Allow me to apologize for my 
discourtesy earlier. It was completely 
unbefitting of a champion.
140:
So please, Alice. Come back down and
enjoy the pancakes we've prepared.
144:
Hmph. See? That wasn't so hard, was 
it?
155: I just felt bad for Light, that's all.
159:
Yes, yes. Now we can enjoy our 
pancakes together.
162: Let's get going before they get cold!
166:
Very well then. By the way, mine will 
come with extra cream, of course?
